      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change <2% between successive refinement levels; Richardson extrapolation applied.",
      "rationale": "Four-level mesh refinement study performed on the pedicle screw-rod construct. Construct stiffness and yield force QoIs changed by 1.3% and 1.7% respectively between the two finest meshes. Richardson extrapolation applied; estimated discretization error 0.8%. Final mesh selected at refinement level 3 (approximately 420,000 tetrahedral elements). Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance checked.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) employed for linear load steps; iterative solver with preconditioned conjugate gradient used for nonlinear increments. Force residual norm below 1e-6 at every converged increment. Energy balance error less than 0.05% across all analyses. No solver warnings or unconverged increments recorded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments completed; checklist signed.",
      "rationale": "Independent reviewer (second FEA engineer not involved in model construction) reviewed boundary condition definitions, material property assignments, contact pair specifications, and loading protocol against ASTM F1717 standard. Discrepancies identified and resolved prior to production runs. Signed review checklist archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V) validated against coupon data; contact formulation justified.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model for Ti-6Al-4V calibrated against five tensile coupon specimens (mean yield stress 930 MPa, UTS 1000 MPa). Augmented Lagrange contact formulation used at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces; frictionless contact assumption justified by lubricated test conditions per ASTM F1717. Model form consistent with prior FDA FEA guidance for spinal implants."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric parameters sourced from traceable measurements; input uncertainty characterised via propagation analysis referencing a screening sensitivity study.",
      "rationale": "Geometric dimensions measured via CMM on five production screws (mean ± 1 SD reported). Material properties (elastic modulus, yield stress, tangent modulus) sourced from certified mill certificates and supplemental coupon testing. Input uncertainty was characterised through a Monte Carlo propagation study (n=1000 samples) covering elastic modulus, yield stress, and screw root diameter. The UQ report narratively references a screening sensitivity study that ranked elastic modulus and root diameter as dominant contributors; however, the structured sensitivity analysis object has not been separately encoded in this package. Overall input uncertainty contribution to QoI variance is reported as ±3.1% (1σ) for construct stiffness."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens from production lots; lot traceability documented; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (Lab A: n=6, Lab B: n=5). All specimens from the same production lot (lot traceability documented). CMM dimensional inspection of three specimens per lab confirmed conformance to engineering drawing within ±0.05 mm. Sample size exceeds minimum required for Medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least two distinct test conditions (e.g., load levels or configurations) exercised to characterise condition sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol at one load rate and one environmental condition (ambient, dry). A second test condition (e.g., elevated temperature or alternative load rate) was not exercised. This factor is below the required level 3; the shortfall is acknowledged and represents the one identified gap in this credibility assessment. Compensating evidence from the multi-laboratory design partially offsets the limitation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters demonstrably derived from or traceable to the same physical specimens used in testing; mapping documented.",
      "rationale": "Geometric model constructed from CAD nominal dimensions adjusted by CMM measurements of the actual test specimens. Material properties assigned from mill certificates corresponding to the production lot of the tested specimens. Input parameter mapping table cross-referencing FEA inputs to experimental measurement sources reviewed and approved. Equivalency of input parameters confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percentage difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) satisfy both acceptance criteria: maximum percentage difference 7.8%, maximum E/uval 1.41. Validation uncertainty uval computed per ASME V&V 10.1 incorporating experimental measurement uncertainty, inter-laboratory variability, and FEA numerical uncertainty. Output comparison factor achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly correspond to clinical performance endpoints and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly characterise the structural performance endpoints relevant to clinical safety (resistance to fatigue, resistance to permanent deformation). Relevance is high and well-established in the regulatory literature."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, loading, and boundary conditions match or bound the COU scenario; any differences justified.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity replicates the COU scenario directly: same implant geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw), same loading protocol (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending), same boundary conditions (UHMWPE blocks, 44 mm pedicle screw spacing). No extrapolation beyond the validated domain is required for the intended regulatory use. Relevance of validation activities to COU is confirmed at the highest applicable level for this model risk tier."
    }
