    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium model risk, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence COU. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; compensating evidence from the multi-laboratory experimental design and the conservative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, <10% QoI difference) is judged sufficient to support regulatory acceptance. UQ has been performed and the overall input uncertainty contribution is within acceptable bounds. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the stated COU.",
